This page is under construction!

In addition to taking startlingly mediocre photos, I’m also trying to fulfill my desire for delayed gratification by working on my photo development techniques. Thus far, I’ve used the Cinestill DF96 Monobath, which combines developer and fixer in an easy-to-use, grainy solution.

I shoot primarily on Kodak negatives, and have only developed ISO100 so far (my first ISO400 roll experienced a user-caused loading error, and I ended up with an entirely blank roll).
